19/08/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Office of the High Representative on Thursday (18 August) praised the regional action that resulted in the arrest of Bosnian Serb businessman Momcilo Mandic, a former aide to Radovan Karadzic. 
Mandic was detained in Montenegro and extradited to BiH. 
According to OHR spokesperson Ljiljana Radetic, the operation proved the importance of regional co-operation in fighting crime.
In other news Thursday, the EU Police Mission and the Office of the High Representative called for restraint following an incident involving two guards at the Metaljka border crossing between BiH and Serbia-Montenegro. 
On Wednesday, a Serb guard was killed by a Bosniak colleague. 
Bosnian Serb villagers in the border area responded with protests and blocked roads, claiming it was an ethnic attack. 
(Nezavisne novine - 19/08/05; PBS BiH, RTRS, Fena - 18/08/05)
